Stay at home
Only go outside for food, health reasons or work (but only if you cannot work from home)
If you go out, stay 2 metres (6ft) away from other people at all times
Wash your hands as soon as you get home
Do not meet others, even friends or family.
You can spread the virus even if you don’t have symptoms.

India’s land borders are closed and international flights are suspended until 3 May 2020. There are currently no commercial options available to leave India.
UK special flights
The UK government has arranged a fifth round of special charter flights from 5 May to 11 May. There are currently no further flights planned, but we will keep this under review.
British Nationals normally resident in the UK, and Non-British Nationals travelling with close family members who are British Nationals, are currently being prioritised for these flights.
Your eligibility, including your UK address, will be checked before your tickets are issued.
Vulnerable British nationals will continue to be prioritised for these flights.
Vulnerable non-British UK Residents with Indefinite Leave to Remain, and other Foreign Nationals, may only be accommodated if there is sufficient capacity.
Details of all scheduled charter flights can be found below.
All booking portals have now closed.
If you registered for a flight before the booking portal closed, you have been placed on a waiting list. Those on the waiting list who are eligible to fly will be contacted directly by our travel partner CTM when their booking is confirmed and sent information on how to get to airports and flight itineraries.
